      "bodyHtml": "<p class=\"mission-entry-kicker\">SOL 082 / 2026-07-01</p>\n            <h3>Mission Log 010 - SEM training, conductive mounting, carbon coating, and first SEM-EDS reconnaissance</h3>\n            <p>\n              On 1 July, I attended SEM training and prepared the ion-milled Orgueil CI1 section for initial SEM observation. The sample was first fixed onto the SEM specimen stub using carbon tape. To improve electrical continuity between the resin-mounted sample and the stub, aluminium tape was also attached from both sides of the resin portion to the specimen stage.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              After mounting, the sample surface was carbon-coated five times to suppress charging during SEM imaging and EDS analysis. The estimated total coating thickness was approximately 125&nbsp;&Aring;. Preliminary SE and BSE images were then acquired with the Hitachi S-3400 SEM at 15&nbsp;kV, with working distances of approximately 5.8-5.9&nbsp;mm and magnifications of x700 to x1000.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The first SEM-EDS reconnaissance identified several candidate phases and textural domains. Bright BSE grains gave Fe-S or Fe-Ni-S signals and are treated here as pyrrhotite or Fe-sulphide candidates. A Fe-rich oxide signal is recorded as a magnetite candidate. A Ca-Mg-C-O point is a promising carbonate candidate, and Mg-Si-Fe-Al-S-bearing areas are treated as matrix-like material. These identifications remain preliminary and need systematic follow-up before being used as final mineral assignments.\n            </p>\n            <div class=\"mission-data-table-wrap\" aria-label=\"SEM-EDS reconnaissance summary\">\n              <table class=\"mission-data-table\">\n                <caption>SEM-EDS reconnaissance summary</caption>\n                <thead>\n                  <tr><th>Target</th><th>Signal / composition</th><th>Working interpretation</th><th>Status</th></tr>\n                </thead>\n                <tbody>\n                  <tr><td>Bright BSE grains</td><td>Fe-S, locally Fe-Ni-S</td><td>Pyrrhotite / Fe-sulphide candidate</td><td>Preliminary</td></tr>\n                  <tr><td>Fe-rich oxide point</td><td>Fe-O dominant</td><td>Magnetite candidate</td><td>Preliminary</td></tr>\n                  <tr><td>Carbonate-like point</td><td>Ca-Mg-C-O</td><td>Dolomite-related carbonate candidate</td><td>Promising target</td></tr>\n                  <tr><td>Fine-grained domain</td><td>Mg-Si-Fe-Al-S</td><td>Matrix-like altered material</td><td>Context area</td></tr>\n                </tbody>\n              </table>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"mission-log-subsection\">\n              <h4>EDS reconnaissance evidence</h4>\n              <p>\n                The following EDS evidence images connect the reconnaissance table to the original point spectra and element maps. They are used here as preliminary target and context records, not as final mineral assignments.\n              </p>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"mission-photo-grid four\">\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-01.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-01.jpg\" alt=\"SE image of the prepared Orgueil CI1 section at x1000\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 1 - SE image of the prepared section after conductive mounting and carbon coating.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-02.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-02.jpg\" alt=\"BSE image of the prepared Orgueil CI1 section at x1000\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 2 - BSE image of the same observation field, showing compositional contrast among grains and matrix.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-03.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-03.jpg\" alt=\"SE image of a bright particle and surrounding matrix-like area\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 3 - SE view of a bright particle and surrounding matrix-like material selected for reconnaissance.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-04.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-04.jpg\" alt=\"BSE image of the same particle-rich reconnaissance area\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 4 - BSE view of the particle-rich reconnaissance area used to guide EDS point analysis and mapping.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-09.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-09.jpg\" alt=\"Ca-Mg-C-O carbonate candidate with approximately 1 to 1 Ca to Mg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 5 - Ca-Mg-C-O carbonate candidate; Ca:Mg is approximately 1:1, making this the key dolomite-related target from the first SEM-EDS reconnaissance.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-05.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-05.jpg\" alt=\"EDS spectrum and BSE target for the Fe-sulphide candidate\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 6 - Fe-Ni-S point analysis used as a Fe-sulphide candidate record.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-06.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-06.jpg\" alt=\"EDS spectrum and BSE target for the Fe-rich oxide candidate\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 7 - Fe-O point analysis used as a Fe-rich oxide candidate record.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-07.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-07.jpg\" alt=\"EDS spectrum and BSE target for matrix-like altered material\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 8 - Mg-Si-Fe-Al-S point analysis used as a matrix-like altered material record.</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-08.jpg\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260701-08.jpg\" alt=\"Ca-rich EDS map and Fe-S EDS map with Si-Mg-O matrix context\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\"><figcaption>Fig. 9 - Ca-rich EDS map, Fe-S EDS map, and Si-Mg-O matrix context for the mapped reconnaissance field.</figcaption></figure>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"log-tags\">\n              <span>SEM training</span>\n              <span>Carbon tape</span>\n              <span>Aluminium tape</span>\n              <span>Carbon coating</span>\n              <span>SEM-EDS</span>\n              <span>Dolomite candidate</span>\n              <span>Pyrrhotite candidate</span>\n              <span>Magnetite candidate</span>\n              <span>Matrix</span>\n              <span>Carbonate candidate</span>\n            </div>\n            <a class=\"mission-back-to-index\" href=\"#mission-index\">Back to Mission Index</a>"
