    "bodyHtml": "<p class=\"mission-entry-kicker\">SOL 020 / 2026-04-20</p>\n            <h3>Mission Log 002 · Orgueil particles embedded in Petropoxy 154</h3>\n            <p>\n              I received Orgueil particles from Professor Takashi Mikouchi and carried out resin embedding at\n              The University Museum, The University of Tokyo. The particles were embedded using Petropoxy 154\n              in preparation for subsequent cutting, mounting, and polishing.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              After vacuum impregnation, the embedded sample was kept at 80&nbsp;°C for one day to allow the\n              resin to cure. This step was intended to stabilise the fragile Orgueil material before mechanical\n              processing.\n            </p>\n            <div class=\"mission-photo-grid four\">\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-01.jpg\" alt=\"Petropoxy 154 resin used for embedding the Orgueil particles\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-01.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-01.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-01.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 1 · Resin used for embedding</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-02.jpg\" alt=\"Selected Orgueil meteorite particles for the experiment\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-02.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-02.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-02.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 2 · Selected meteorite particles</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-03.jpg\" alt=\"Orgueil particles after resin addition, before vacuum impregnation\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-03.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-03.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-03.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 3 · Particles after resin addition, before vacuum</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-04.jpg\" alt=\"Vacuum impregnation of the resin and Orgueil particles\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-04.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-04.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-04.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 4 · Vacuum impregnation</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-05.jpg\" alt=\"Overnight curing of the embedded sample at 80 degrees Celsius\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-05.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-05.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-05.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 5 · Overnight curing at 80&nbsp;°C</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-06.jpg\" alt=\"Close-up observation of the embedded particles on the heating plate\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-06.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-06.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-06.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 6 · Close-up of particles on the heating plate</figcaption></figure>\n              <figure><img class=\"mission-thumb-img\" src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-07.jpg\" alt=\"Orgueil particles used in this experiment and their approximate size\" data-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-07.jpg\" data-thumb-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-07.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" data-mobile-full-src=\"assets/img/grad-log-20260420-07.jpg\"><figcaption>Fig. 7 · Particles used in this experiment and their size</figcaption></figure>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"log-tags\">\n              <span>Orgueil</span>\n              <span>Petropoxy 154</span>\n              <span>Vacuum impregnation</span>\n              <span>80&nbsp;°C curing</span>\n              <span>The University Museum</span>\n            </div>\n                <a class=\"mission-back-to-index\" href=\"#mission-index\">Back to Mission Index ↑</a>",
